beer.beer_description: The California Gold Rush lured thousands west to "see the elephant,"a 19th-century metaphor for the hopeful but risky pursuit of happiness, adventure, and fortune. Made with 2-row barley malt and fresh whole-cone hops, its bright amber color, distinctively complex aroma, spiky bitterness, malty depth, and clean finish unite to create a uniquely flavorful, memorable, and timeless IPA.
